data.title: will.i.am
data.meta_description: Read all about will.i.am with TV Guide's exclusive biography including their list of awards, celeb facts and more at TV Guide.
data.text:
Fast Facts

In the early 1990s, he formed the hip-hop group Atban Klann with Allan Pineda Lindo

A few years later, the band morphed into the Black Eyed Peas

Created a clothing line in 2001

Cowrote the song "Ordinary People" with John Legend, the singer's 2005 breakout hit single

In 2007, released his solo album Songs About Girls

Was the first recipient of the Daytime Emmy Award for Best New Approaches in Daytime Entertainment, a category that was added in 2008

He won for his hugely popular "Yes We Can" presidential campaign music video for Democratic candidate Barack Obama

In his film debut, he provided the voice for the character of Moto Moto in the 2008 animated movie Madagascar: Escape 2 Africa
